Function: f(x) = (1/2)*x'*Q*x - b'*x

An example Conjugate Gradient Method:
 
         x'*Q*x = 0
  
         x = alpha*x + ... + alpha^{k-1}*x^{k-1}

         x'*Q*x = alpha*x + ... + alpha^{k-1}*x^{k-1}

         Minimal solutions: x = 0, roots{(alpha + ... + (k-1)*alpha^{k-1}*x^{k-2}-2*Q*x)

         The general solution includes imaginary values and an nth root polynomial. 

         Also, extensive solutions in conjugate gradient method literature involve further m-dimensional spaces (x,y,z,++), mutual directionals (x1,x2,...xn), and multi-directional systems (x1, x2, x3,...).

